The paper discusses the development of a unified experimental framework for computer systems research and development, which involves interdisciplinary knowledge and technology transfer between academia and industry. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE), Architecture (cs.AR), Programming Languages (cs.PL), Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. However, since the paper focuses on developing a workflow for autotuning and machine learning techniques, cs.SE and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories.
